criteria.inclusion_criteria:
1. children refractory lung diseases;
2. cannot be healed by conventional drug therapy;
3. informed consent signed by parents and/or patients(>14years old).

criteria.exclusion_criteria:
1. complex congenital heart disease;
2. WHO class III or IV pulmonary hypertension;
3. congenital respiratory tract malformations;
4. congenital anomaly of nervous system;
5. hereditary diseases;
6. HIV infected/viral hepatitis/tuberculosis/ syphilis;
7. severe or uncontrolled infection not expected to survive 2 weeks;
8. active pneumorrhagia or tension pneumothorax;
9. malignant diseases;
10. patient participating or having participated in a clinical trial with another investigation drugs.
